Subject: [PATCH] fix(email): localize fromNow/fallbacks using general.defaultLanguage

email.service.ts hardcoded `const lang = ""`, which overrides the
SystemLanguageResolver (general.defaultLanguage) and makes nestjs-i18n
fall back to "en-US". As a result email expiry times (moment().fromNow())
and i18n fallbacks always render in English regardless of the configured
default language. Introduced in PR #70 ("site wide default language
support"), whose own message lists "fix(email): use language locale for
time from now" -- the exact behavior `lang = ""` defeats.

--- a/backend/src/email/email.service.ts
+++ b/backend/src/email/email.service.ts
@@ -70,7 +70,7 @@
     const shareUrl = `${this.config.get(
       "general.appUrl",
     )}/s/${shareId}?recipient=${encodeURIComponent(recipientId)}`;
-    const lang = "";
+    const lang = this.config.get("general.defaultLanguage");
     const locale = this.i18n.translate("email.locale", { lang });

     await this.sendMail(
